<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-229-656  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 229 656.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  March 12 1990 n291 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FCC slates ATandamp;T reforms. (Federal Communications Commission)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Killette, Kathleen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Federal Communications Commission (FCC) proposes reforms inthe way AT and T is regulated.andP;  The proposed rule changes, madefeasible because of a more competitive long distance market, wouldallow AT and T to respond more quickly to challenges fromcompeting communications service suppliers.andP;  The new rules wouldapply to '800' numbers as well as operator services andinternational switched services.andP;  The changed regulations wouldrequire that AT and T disclose more details about customercontracts.andP;  The FCC plans to study the long distance market interms of market share, supply capabilities, financial strength,and the size and status of users.andP;  Also under consideration is amove to allow AT and T to bundle customer premises equipment andenhanced services.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (rules and regulations).andO;Ticker:    T.andO;Topic:     United States. Federal Communications CommissionGovernment RegulationCommunications Service SuppliersCompetitionIndustry AnalysisTelephone Companies.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>